---
title: "Figure 5.5: Sequence Diagram — Multi-Step Career Profiling and Algorithm Execution"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant B as Browser
    participant PH as PortalRequestHandler
    participant CK as Cookie Store
    participant RA as run_algorithm
    participant DB as Database

    B->>PH: GET /profile/step1
    PH-->>B: Render profile_step1.html

    B->>PH: POST /profile/step1 (math_grade, english_grade, ... 7 grades)
    PH->>CK: Set-Cookie: step1_data = JSON(grades)
    PH-->>B: Redirect to /profile/step2

    B->>PH: GET /profile/step2
    PH-->>B: Render profile_step2.html

    B->>PH: POST /profile/step2 (problem_solving, rating_analytical, ... 7 ratings)
    PH->>CK: Set-Cookie: step2_data = JSON(skills)
    PH-->>B: Redirect to /profile/step3

    B->>PH: GET /profile/step3
    PH-->>B: Render profile_step3.html

    B->>PH: POST /profile/step3 (work_environment, industry_interests, budget, ...)
    PH->>CK: Set-Cookie: step3_data = JSON(preferences)
    PH-->>B: Redirect to /profile/step4

    B->>PH: GET /profile/step4
    PH->>CK: Read step1_data, step2_data, step3_data
    PH-->>B: Render profile_step4.html (review summary)

    B->>PH: POST /profile/submit
    PH->>CK: Read step1_data + step2_data + step3_data
    PH->>RA: run_algorithm(profile_data)
    RA-->>PH: Top 8 career matches with match_pct

    PH->>DB: UPDATE users SET last_results = JSON(results), profile_data = JSON(profile)
    DB-->>PH: OK

    PH-->>B: Render recommendations.html (top career matches)
